<topic template="JinTone2-Template" lasteditedby="win7" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Zero Sequence</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">Zero_Sequence</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Zero Sequence</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;" translate="true">This module aim to quickly verification the fixed value of single phase fault of zero-sequence relays with definite time characteristic.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading HowTo_atoc_"><text styleclass="Heading HowTo_atoc_" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;" translate="true">Prerequisites for testing</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;" translate="true">It is not necessary set the Test Object prior to testing.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;" translate="true">Define the hardware, the routing and wiring and trip commands.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;" translate="true">According the relay settings fill to the &quot;Setting&quot; tab.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;" translate="true">Set times and fault trigger mode etc on &quot;Parameters&quot; tab.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;" translate="true">Adding test points by click on the zero-sequence characteristic plane, or enter the test point parameters into the input fields &quot;I fault&quot;, &quot;I fault %&quot;, &quot;V fault&quot;, &quot;angle&quot;, &quot;Segment&quot; by keyboard entry. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;" translate="true">Or use &quot;Add to...&quot; button to quickly add multiple test points for any zero-sequence segments and fault types.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
